results.name: Number of repeated remainders arising when n is divided by all primes up to n: a(n) = pi(n) - A073453(n).
link: G. C. Greubel, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..1000
example: n=25: Primes are (2,3,5,7,11,13,17,19,23), remainders are (1,1,0,4,3,12,8,6,2), distinct remainders are {0,1,2,3,4,6,8,12} which has 8 members, so a(25) = 9 - 8 = 1.
program: (PARI) a(n) = my(P=primes([2, n])); #P - #Set(apply(p->n%p, P)) \\ _Charles R Greathouse IV_, Jun 17 2016
